  <datafield tag="545" ind1="0" ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Pioneer broadcasting executive with several broadcasting entities, but mainly with WGN Continental Broadcasting Co. (now Tribune Broadcasting Co.). From 1949 to 1952, Quaal was executive director of the Clear Channel Broadcasting Service in Washington DC. He later served as president and chief executive officer of the Service from 1964 to 1974. In 1952, Quaal joined the Crosley Broadcasting Corp. as assistant general manager, later vice president and general manager of Crosley's radio, television and short wave properties. In 1956, he returned to WGN (where he had begun his career in 1941) as vice president and general manager. Then in 1963, he was elected president of the Company. In 1975, he retired to form Ward L. Quaal Company, a broadcasting consultation and lobbying service.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="520" ind1="2" ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Scrapbooks (with index), 1941-2004, consisting of clippings, photographs, published materials, and memorabilia from all phases of his career; also biographical information and photocopies of letters received from presidents; and DVD and CD-ROm with photographs celebrating his life and career.</subfield>
